        <div n="086-570B">
          <head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-086-570B-headnote-1">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-086-570B-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-086-570B-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">by D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Swift.</l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-086-570B-headnote-2">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-086-570B-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-086-570B-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-086-570B-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-086-570B-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-086-570B-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-1" n="1">When Mother Clud had rose from play,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-2" n="2">And call'd to take y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Cards away,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-3" n="3">Van saw, but seem'd not to regard,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-4" n="4">How Miss pick't ev'ry painted Card,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-5" n="5">And busy both with Hand &amp; Eye</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-6" n="6">Soon rear'd a House two Stories high.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-7" n="7">Van's Genius, without Thought or Lecture,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-8" n="8">This highly turn'd to Architecture.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-9" n="9">He saw y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Edifice &amp; smil'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-10" n="10">Vow'd it was pretty for a Child;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-11" n="11">It was so perfect in its Kind,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-12" n="12">He kept y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> model in his Mind.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-13" n="13">But when he found y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Boys at play</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-14" n="14">And saw them dabling of their Clay,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-15" n="15">He stood behind a stall to lurke</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-16" n="16">And mark y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> progress of their work:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-17" n="17">With true delight observ'd 'em all</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-18" n="18">Raking up mud to build a wall.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-19" n="19">The plan he much admired, &amp; took</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-20" n="20">The Model in his Table-Book;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-21" n="21">Thought himself now exactly skill'd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-22" n="22">And so resolv'd a House to build:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-23" n="23">A real House, with rooms &amp; Stairs</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-24" n="24">Five times at lest as big as theirs</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-25" n="25">Taller then Miss's by two Yards,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-26" n="26">Not a sham thing of Clay &amp; Cards:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-27" n="27">And so he did, for in a while</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-28" n="28">He built up such a monstrous pile,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-29" n="29">That no two chairmen could be found</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-30" n="30">Able to lift it from y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Ground.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-31" n="31">Still at Whitehall it stands in view</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-32" n="32">Just in y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> place where first it grew.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-33" n="33">There all y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> little Schoolboys run</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-34" n="34">Envying to see themselves outdone.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-35" n="35">From such deep rudiments as these</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-36" n="36">Van is become by due degrees</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-37" n="37">For building famed, &amp; justly reckon'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-38" n="38">At Court Vitruvius the Second.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-39" n="39">No wonder, since wise Authors sh\o·<hi rend="italics">over</hi>·e\w,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-40" n="40">That best foundations should be low.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-41" n="41">And now y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Duke has wisely ta'ne him</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-42" n="42">To be his Architect at Blenheim.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-43" n="43">But Raillery for once apart</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-44" n="44">If this Rule holds in ev'ry Art;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-45" n="45">Or if his Grace were no more skill'd in</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-46" n="46">The Art of batt'ring Walls than building</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-47" n="47">We might expect to find next Year</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-570B-line-48" n="48">A mouse-trap-man chief Engineer.</l>
          </lg>
